<p>On top of being sleep-deprived, I was now hungry and sweating profusely. Blundering my way ever-forward, I stumbled upon a strong and vibrant south Indian and Bangladeshi community in the <em>Masjid India</em> (aka <em>Little India</em>) corner of Kuala Lumpur. I walked into a restaurant hoping for a strong <em>desi chai</em> to keep me awake. The boy who served me — a young boy in his late teens from Tamil Nadu — suggested I try their traditional food, served in their traditional manner: on the leaf of a banana tree.</p>
<div id="fig-bananafood" class="quarto-float quarto-figure quarto-figure-center anchored">
