<p>Insofar as temperature and relative humidity are concerned, Kuala Lumpur is quite monoclimatic year-round. At 80% relative humidity, no wonder you feel so hot: with the air already saturated with water, it is difficult for your sweat to evaporate and transfer the thermal energy into the surroundings.</p>
</section>
